description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the new GI Unit at Salisbury NHS Foundation Trust. The Clinical Nurse Specialist Practitioner (CNSP) will be an experienced practitioner who is able to demonstrate a very high degree of autonomy and complex decision making based on an application and interpretation of broad clinical policies, with a personal and professional skill in Inflammatory bowel disease (IBD).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post-holder will be required to manage clinical care and be accountable for their area of practice and be an independent prescriber. Working within their own sphere of competence, they will initiate, alter and stop medication related to their field of practice as determined by assessment and in line with relevant clinical guidelines. The post will be essential to leading on the clinical, educational and professional direction of the IBD service, ensuring the needs of the patient are placed at the centre of care delivery. They will manage the IBD Nursing Team and the Benign Specialist Nurses within the GI Unit, providing support, appraisals and direction to these CNS’s.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Henry wilding, Divisional Head of Nursing - hwilding@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;01722 336262 x 4438&lt;/p&gt;
